The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 November is 8,913 (1,031.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 November, there were 800 new confirmed cases (92.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 November, there were 1,055 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (255 fewer cases).
